ephenjay\">@stephenjay#50</POSTMENTION> POD贡献度证明何时上星云公链？我期待POD共识机制早日上线。</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.68.143.9',0,1),(128,20,12,'2019-01-10 12:25:51',37,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"20\" displayname=\"starkstay\" id=\"66\" number=\"7\" username=\"starkstay\">@starkstay#66</POSTMENTION> As a user, you will not get the DIP reward. However, you may help some developers test their DApps on testnet. And that will be very helpful for the stability of Nebulas Nova. <br/>\nFor how to use the DApp on testnet, you may contact the developers. And we may also list the testing DApps in our community.</p>\n</r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'108.162.215.139',0,1),(129,16,35,'2019-01-10 12:26:56',116,'comment','<t><p>我的NAS钱包地址在Nova中搜不到什么NR指数情况？</p></t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.68.143.9',0,1),(130,20,13,'2019-01-10 12:27:02',37,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"20\" displayname=\"satoshibytes\" id=\"93\" number=\"8\" username=\"satoshibytes\">@satoshibytes#93</POSTMENTION> The NR on the testnest is separated form the NR on the mainnet. The accumulated tokens can somewhat influence the fairness of the DIP testnet . However the main purpose of the testnet activity is to improve the stability of the DIP.  Later in the mainnet the fairness of the DIP protocol can be still guaranteed.</p> </r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'108.162.215.139',0,1),(131,16,36,'2019-01-10 12:34:45',136,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"16\" displayname=\"zhaozeen\" id=\"103\" number=\"16\" username=\"zhaozeen\">@zhaozeen#103</POSTMENTION> <br/>\n感谢你的问题，币价的涨跌没办法由项目方来决定，很大程度上跟随市场的变化。作为公链项目，我们也始终对市场保持敬畏。</p>\n\n<p>用币价来激发和维持开发者的热情并不持久，而且也不符合开发者的利益最大化。我们核心是公链的底层技术，我们会不断地优化主网的性能，完善开发者需要的文档和工具，更重要的是，我们会通过DIP给予开发者提供链上原生的、持续、公平的激励。另外，我们也会利用星云链自身和外部的资源，为我们的生态开发者对接流量入口，对接用户资源。培养起来真正可持续的良性发展的生态。这也是我们在区块链行业这么多年收获到的经验。</p>\n\n<p>进入2019年，区块链行业未来的突破来自于对终端用户即Token User的深刻理解。token holder基础来自于token的交互，不是单纯的token holder的交易，也不是单纯的开发者的开发，而是更加完善和丰富的闭环生态。只有满足了token user的需求，做到对token user友好，公链项目才能成功，这也将是星云持续努力的方向</p>\n</r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'103.22.200.129',0,1),(132,16,37,'2019-01-10 12:39:21',126,'comment','<t><p>根据最新的路线图，开发进度往后推了一年。是开发过程中遇到了技术瓶颈还是其他原因？</p>\n</t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.68.253.176',0,1),(133,16,38,'2019-01-10 12:41:47',136,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"16\" displayname=\"antsky\" id=\"110\" number=\"21\" username=\"antsky\">@antsky#110</POSTMENTION> <br/>\n很好的问题，我们一直在推进和商业伙伴层面的合作，在NOVA上线之后，星云为区块链世界提供了很多独创的功能。包括价值尺度NR的实现，去中心化自动化原生激励DIP的推进以及可以给区块链提供无缝升级能力的NBRE的实现。这些特性诞生之初就是源于我们对区块链行业痛点的认知。在他们实现之后，我们也看到了很多迫切需要的落地场景。</p>\n\n<p>以NBRE为例，区块链的“硬分叉”升级伴随的社区的分裂和共识坍缩的问题一直是公有链甚至是联盟链项目的一大痛点，这也使得区块链中的很多创新无法顺利进行。NBRE的特性使得“主网升级”这一操作成为常态，再微小的创新都不再有来自“主网升级”的压力。NBRE所带来平滑的“主网升级”的能力，就具备很大的落地的场景和商业推进的空间</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.68.133.225',0,1),(134,16,39,'2019-01-10 12:52:53',149,'comment','<t> <p>问题。人文社会是基于复杂高效的分工协作产生更高价值，区块链存在的意义是有大规模可监督的需求，星云链什么时候可以增加出非开发者参与建设区块链的工作机会？（例如协作场景下的社交，文化交流，旅游信息等）像这种‘链上公民’和开发者激励的权重分配是怎样比例的（粒度、量级），若能否打通‘链上公民’和应用开发者的协作桥梁，能否实现链上契约处置？‘链上公民’的委员会，比如‘发展方向委员会’‘激励规则委员会’‘公正委员会’这类分权机构是否公开，是招用制度还是有效意见抓取制度？最后，打算如何发挥区块链的天然跨境优势，目标国家和地区有哪些？</p></t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'103.22.200.177',0,1),(135,16,40,'2019-01-10 13:00:34',37,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"16\" displayname=\"chenshiyan\" id=\"127\" number=\"34\" username=\"chenshiyan\">@chenshiyan#127</POSTMENTION> 具体的时间目前仍然不能给出，团队目前在进行理论验证工作</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.58.18',0,1),(136,16,41,'2019-01-10 13:01:34',37,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"16\" displayname=\"chenshiyan\" id=\"129\" number=\"35\" username=\"chenshiyan\">@chenshiyan#129</POSTMENTION> NAS钱包中的NR指数目前还不支持，在Nova上线主网之后，我们会对钱包进行更新，以便查看NR指数。</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.58.18',0,1),(137,16,42,'2019-01-10 13:05:01',126,'comment','<t><p>国家互联网信息办公室刚发布了《区块链信息服务管理规定》，星云链有把握符合规范吗？</p>\n</t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.179.247',0,1),(138,16,43,'2019-01-10 13:13:26',148,'comment','<t><p>钱包功能太弱，这个以后是流量入口，应该加入星云指数原生搜索，整合入主流货币行情及主流货币星云指数top10，钱包实名奖励NAS，有利以后形成生态闭环</p></t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.179.247',0,1),(139,16,44,'2019-01-10 13:13:26',148,'comment','<t><p>钱包功能太弱，这个以后是流量入口，应该加入星云指数原生搜索，整合入主流货币行情及主流货币星云指数top10，钱包实名奖励NAS，有利以后形成生态闭环</p></t>',NULL,NULL,'2019-01-10 13:13:42',148,'162.158.179.247',0,1),(141,16,45,'2019-01-10 13:41:04',17,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"16\" displayname=\"jiangzeting\" id=\"137\" number=\"42\" username=\"jiangzeting\">@jiangzeting#137</POSTMENTION> 今天出台的仅是一个管理规定，还没有具体的细则和操作规范，所以我个人的观点是，可以参考美国对于Fintech行业的监管情况，游戏有公开透明清晰的规则，更利于可持续进行和发展。</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.68.132.170',0,1),(142,16,46,'2019-01-10 13:52:56',150,'comment','<t><p>在目前的大环境里依然初心不改积极迭代<br/>\n对星云团队表示敬佩！支持你们！</p>\n\n<p>我是非开发者，所以技术上的问题提不出来呀<br/>\n就希望你们举一个实际的例子<br/>\n说明一下星云到底能做什么</p>\n\n<p>我大概知道一个是可以通过星云的价值体系将目前混乱的链上数据具象化，给出活跃度呀贡献度呀这些维度的定量评价。那这种评价的最终好处是什么呢？目前比如谷歌通过它的一套逻辑，可以做到精准投放广告呀优化搜索排名呀这些事，可以直接服务于它的盈利。星云的这种对链上数据的整理，最终是希望指向一个什么目的呢？</p>\n\n<p>二就是针对开发者友好的原生激励环境。我能想到的当然就是能大量吸引开发者咯，那开发者吸引来了后星云就会（至少）变成一个dapp市场。所以还想请问星云希望借助自己dapp市场的这一面角色去做哪些事？</p>\n\n<p>纯小白的疑问咯<br/>\n长期持有NAS中</p>\n\n</t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.68.146.53',0,1),(143,16,47,'2019-01-10 14:04:08',17,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"16\" displayname=\"Ravin\" id=\"134\" number=\"39\" username=\"Ravin\">@Ravin#134</POSTMENTION> 很有质量的问题，我个人理解，对于具体场景的应用探索不是星云链着重发力的方向。星云链现在还是应该专注于自己核心能力——底层公链技术，以及对于社区化的探索。但是Ravin提到的这些问题，我认为很值得讨论，这些问题更适用于整个公链行业。</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.68.133.225',0,1),(144,16,48,'2019-01-10 14:04:42',31,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"16\" displayname=\"jiangzeting\" id=\"132\" number=\"37\" username=\"jiangzeting\">@jiangzeting#132</POSTMENTION> 你好呀。开发进度没有往后推一年哦。具体研究路线图和开发路线图参见<URL url=\"https://nebulas.io/cn/roadmap.html\"><s>[</s>官网路线图页面<e>](https://nebulas.io/cn/roadmap.html)</e></URL>。<br/>\n本来星云原力绿皮书的发布和星云原力（NF）的实现就是2019年。事实上2018年底随着Nebulas NOVA上线，还提前完成了星云区块链可执行环境（NBRE），使区块链核心协议可即时升级。在可升级自进化的道路上迈开了第一步。<br/>\n至于贡献度证明（PoD）的实现时间，我希望大家可以理解，对工程开发来说，越近的版本越细致，几年后的话只能是给出大致估算，很难细致到月以下的时间单位。就像火箭发射，大方向登录哪个星球是明确的，但每天都在应对各种内外部变化不断瞄准，需要保持专注，持续不断地调整，才能最终实现目标。<br/>\n我们在2017年的时候清晰给出Eagle Nebula的具体开发路线图和时间表。2018年给出了Nebulas NOVA的，紧接着NF的具体实现节奏今年会给出。星云的开发节奏正常，有序，公布具体发布日期后，从未发生过延误。我们对每一次“瞄准”负责。并同时欢迎社区开发者加入到星云开发中来，让我们一起努力，一起进步。星云是我们大家的。</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.78.247',0,1),(145,16,49,'2019-01-10 14:05:01',17,'discussionLocked','{\"locked\":true}',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1),(146,16,50,'2019-01-10 14:23:47',17,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"16\" displayname=\"paulcheung1999\" id=\"142\" number=\"46\" username=\"paulcheung1999\">@paulcheung1999#142</POSTMENTION> <br/>\n第一个问题，可以把链上的地址和智能合约看做google上的网页，那么链上数据的整理，也是为了给链上的地址做出排名。进而通过开发者激励协议，来给予排名高的地址奖励。这种公开透明的模式是有利于生态开发者的。一个好的激励机制会让生态可持续地发展，壮大。<br/>\n第二个问题来讲，我们希望有社区的同学把dapp市场做起来，而且有多样性的展现。而我们的移动钱包NAS nano也在初期社区不够成熟的时候，为开发者们提供流量的入口，目的也是增加星云链的token user.</p>\n</r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.69.23.90',0,1),(147,20,14,'2019-01-10 15:37:21',128,'comment','<t><p>When will the explorer be updated to include DIP information?</p></t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.75.133',0,1),(148,20,15,'2019-01-10 17:06:35',152,'comment','<r><p>Good day everyone,</p>\n\n<p>First of i wanted to say congratulations and offer my biggest compliments to the team for all their achievements so far. The technology they are developing will be essential to the blockchain world, and i can<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>t praise them enough for always underpromising and overachieving and never missing deadlines, i truly see the potential in this project, given i am a developer going on 15 years career now.</p> \n\n<p>My main question is about adoption and the potential future value growth of the Nebulas ecosystem. It is clear that this bear market has hurt many if not all projects financially and community wise, many past growth gains have been wiped out, but most importantly things have been offly too quiet around the space including around Nebulas that even now it is hard to conduct an AMA and attracting a lot viewers in discussions. Im sure many are still holding NAS coins but are paying less attention to the market and just going with their daily lives.</p> \n\n<p>Given that there are so many protocols in the crypto space right now, without mentioning any names, all competing very heavily to become a central hub for decentralized applications, is the team aware that there needs to be a business and marketing team within the committee to work on strategies to raise brand awareness around Nebulas, and to increase the size of the community which in turn will help grow the ecosystem, thus gaining more dominance within the crypto space?  The DIP program will definitely be a huge factor in terms of us developers being rewarded with NAS coins and potentially acting as supernodes bookkeepers in the future, but does the team have a strategy to help the project and ecosystem gain dominance and market share which in turn will make the NAS asset more valuable over time? I fully understand and praise Hitters<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP> vision for wanting everyone to be equals and not having whales within Nebulas, but does the team care about value growth? It is clear that current market conditions have affected the project<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>s valuation tremendously, but many other project teams believe that in order to grow a community and to attract more developers, the ecosystem needs to gain more popularity and be more in the spotlight and competitive, which in turn will help those developer<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>s dapps gain more attention and adoption. So im hoping to find out if there is a future strategy in place with marketing and business experts in the software development field.</p>  \n\n<p>Thank you very much for your time, and Go Nebulas! <E>:)</E></p> </r>','2019-01-10 17:11:35',152,NULL,NULL,'162.158.126.19',0,1),(149,20,16,'2019-01-10 17:43:34',141,'comment','<r><p>Will Nebulas step up it<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>s marketing, especially for the western world? I don<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>t think there are many in the western world who know Nebulas has thousands of DAPs as now, and how amazing project it is.</p> </r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.63.193',0,1),(150,20,17,'2019-01-10 18:33:08',131,'comment','<t><p>I think the first popular dapps will be solving some market inefficiency that is on the edges of legality. Similar to napster/emule days.</p> \n\n<p>Are you worried about dapps being used in malicious ways? Is nebulas able to stop a malicious dapp from operating by stopping their smart contract addresses? Will it be decentralized in the future such that a dapp could not be stopped?</p></t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.69.69.19',0,1),(151,20,18,'2019-01-10 22:48:12',153,'comment','<t><p>Did the team ever thought about making a hybrid consensus like POS next to POD? The POS consensus can maybe benefit the community by giving them more incentive to hold NAS and also by letting them run a node makes it more decentralized.</p> </t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.150.91',0,1),(152,20,19,'2019-01-10 22:55:22',153,'comment','<t><p>I really would like to have Ledger Nano S or Trezor support for NAS. On telegram i heard there was already someone that claimed the bounty for creating an implementation for this. That was a long time ago. Maybe that person is not part of the community anymore and we wait for nothing to be released. Did the team thought about writing the code themselves? I think your team is absolutelly capable of doing it and maybe it is also more exposure if we are supported on Ledger and Trezor.</p></t>','2019-01-10 22:59:52',153,NULL,NULL,'162.158.150.7',0,1),(153,20,20,'2019-01-10 23:09:45',152,'comment','<r><p>Hey team, i meant to ask also, when PoD is implemented, will the team be researching other methods of scalability such as sharding, sidechains, to ensure that as the network becomes more decentralized that the throughput of txn<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>s still remains powerful? And if so, any chance it will be implemented at the same time as the network transitions over to PoD?</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.126.19',0,1),(154,20,21,'2019-01-10 23:35:43',152,'comment','<r><p>So i<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>ve had a chance today to spend a few hours reading all the conversations of the AMA on the Chinese community channel with the help of Google translate, there are indeed many Chinese supporters whom are very supportive of Nebulas have great hopes for its future success, but just like in the western world, they too seem worried about the massive drop in NAS price, the fact that the performance of NAS has been worrisome throughout the year, not only because of the bear market the price correction of Bitcoin, but also with the first Dapps incentives which led to a massive selloff of NAS tokens.</p> \n\n<p>It is fair to say that the individuals spending time on those community forums and social channels following the progress of Nebulas aren<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>t in it just to make a quick buck, but are indeed in it for the journey and to see the ecosystem flourish and get adopted, and potentially contribute as developers and non-developers. It does however appears that many of Nebulas supporters including developers would like to see commercial enterprise adoption, as well as strategies in place that will in the future see the project experience constant natural value growth, given that despite the amazing technology we are witnessing, we are severely undervalued price wise, while many other networks will be pushing their own incentive grants campaigns to increase adoption and attract developers.</p>\n\n<p>So in order to attract developers being rewarded with NAS, as well as more bookkeepers securing the network in the future, the NAS rewards hopefully will have to show proper valuation. But it appears that the team doesn<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>t seem to care about value growth and would prefer to take a passive approach and just focusing on the tech, which of course is important nonetheless. I<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>m only hoping to fully understand where the team stands in that regard given that many participated in the early days token sale, many developers want to see Nebulas succeed being the giant winner above other projects like NEO, and other blockchains including non-Chinese projects, not to mention also that if different blockchain technologies were to be compared, Nebulas clearly ends up as the clear winner and it should be reflected in its valuation.</p>\n\n<p>Thank you</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.126.115',0,1),(155,20,22,'2019-01-11 03:25:56',37,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"20\" displayname=\"m5j\" id=\"147\" number=\"14\" username=\"m5j\">@m5j#147</POSTMENTION> We will update the explorer to include DIP information on testnet on Jan 20. And the mainnet support will be updated at the end of March.</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.69.33.212',0,1),(156,20,23,'2019-01-11 03:48:53',37,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"20\" displayname=\"starkstay\" id=\"150\" number=\"17\" username=\"starkstay\">@starkstay#150</POSTMENTION> I think this question is really challenging.</p> \n\n<p>We do have some worries about malicious DApps. As a decentralized blockchain project, we follow what the community need.  We believe in the good part of people, and malicious DApps should be very rare.</p> </r>','2019-01-11 03:49:10',37,NULL,NULL,'162.158.58.114',0,1),(157,20,24,'2019-01-11 03:50:41',37,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"20\" displayname=\"Michel\" id=\"151\" number=\"18\" username=\"Michel\">@Michel#151</POSTMENTION> Thanks for your suggestion. PoS has a number of advantages, such as energy-efficiency and resistance for Sybil attack. However, PoS likes to facilitate the Cartel Formation which will lead to unfairness. Besides, the pledge of token results in liquidity degradation. That is the reason for our deliberate choice of the devotion (Nebulas Rank) instead of stake.  Actually, we<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>re looking at designing the consensus protocol and 