keystore is okay. Will you be able to try another account for mining? Btw, did you ever change any code? especially in the <FP char=\"“\">\"</FP>account<FP char=\"”\">\"</FP> and <FP char=\"“\">\"</FP>core<FP char=\"”\">\"</FP> modules?</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.106.93',0,1),(212,47,2,'2019-01-21 23:46:55',116,'comment','<t><p>祝贺，看好星云DIP开发者原生激励。</p></t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.69.33.212',0,1),(213,46,9,'2019-01-22 02:14:49',167,'comment','<r><p>Oh ! yes . I changed the consensus algorithm. <br/>\nRUN sed -i <FP char=\"“\">\"</FP>s/\\= 21/\\= 1/<FP char=\"”\">\"</FP> consensus/dpos/dpos_state.go<br/>\nRUN sed -i <FP char=\"“\">\"</FP>s/ + 1//<FP char=\"”\">\"</FP> consensus/dpos/dpos_state.go</p>\n<H2>RUN sed -i <FP char=\"“\">\"</FP>s/DynastySize<ESC><s>\\</s>*</ESC>2\\/3/DynastySize/<FP char=\"”\">\"</FP> consensus/dpos/dpos_state.go<e>\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------</e></H2>\n<p>In the configuration file, i changed the miner address vs the coinbase address to be 2 different addresses and using the coinbase address, it transferred money. but when I use the miner address to transfer money, it says <FP char=\"“\">\"</FP>invalid private key<FP char=\"”\">\"</FP> error.<br/>\nLet me know why, Pls !</p>\n</r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.68.254.57',0,1),(214,46,10,'2019-01-22 04:35:19',64,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"46\" displayname=\"uranus97s2\" id=\"213\" number=\"9\" username=\"uranus97s2\">@uranus97s2#213</POSTMENTION> <br/>\nI think the reason is:<br/>\nThe miner was unlocked whenever you started the node, and the miner<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>s key was stored in mem. However, later on, when you sent the transaction, it triggered the logic to clear the key in the mem, for more details, you may wanna check the function <FP char=\"“\">\"</FP>SignTransactionWithPassphrase<FP char=\"”\">\"</FP> located in file <FP char=\"“\">\"</FP>account/manager.go<FP char=\"”\">\"</FP>.  And thus, the error shows up when the miner was trying to sign the newly minted block.</p> \n\n<p>So, here are my suggestions:</p>\n<LIST type=\"decimal\"><LI><s>1. </s>If you wanna send transaction out using the miner address, better to use the API <FP char=\"“\">\"</FP>/v1/admin/transaction<FP char=\"”\">\"</FP> (instructions about how to use it can be found in our <URL url=\"https://github.com/nebulasio/wiki/blob/master/tutorials/%5BEnglish%5D%20Nebulas%20101%20-%2002%20Transaction.md#unlock--send\"><s>[</s>tutorial<e>](https://github.com/nebulasio/wiki/blob/master/tutorials/%5BEnglish%5D%20Nebulas%20101%20-%2002%20Transaction.md#unlock--send)</e></URL>), you do not need to unlock the account before sending the transaction since it is already unlocked when launching neb, as I mentioned before.</LI>\n<LI><s>2. </s>A better way is to use another account other than the miner address for sending transactions.</LI></LIST>\n\n<p>Let us know if you have any further questions.</p> </r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.119.14',0,1),(215,46,11,'2019-01-22 04:43:04',167,'comment','<r><p>Thanks for giving me advice, I understand, can I bother you with another question?<br/>\nI have a new problem: that<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>s when I create a new account. If t node is deleted I can re-import another node. If yes, how to import the account?</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.68.253.158',0,1),(216,46,12,'2019-01-22 05:51:40',64,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"46\" displayname=\"uranus97s2\" id=\"215\" number=\"11\" username=\"uranus97s2\">@uranus97s2#215</POSTMENTION></p> \n\n<p>Not sure what do you mean exactly by re-importing another node. In case if you start another node and you wanna re-use the accounts you created before, it<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>s quite easy. Just copy/move the keystore files located in the original go-nebulas/keydir(the path may vary depends on your settings in the config.conf) to the corresponding <FP char=\"“\">\"</FP>keydir<FP char=\"”\">\"</FP> directory in the new code repo.</p> \n\n<p>Hope that solves your concern.</p> </r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'103.22.200.219',0,1),(217,46,13,'2019-01-22 06:26:55',167,'comment','<r><p>Thanks for your respond. I run the node with dockerfile so copying I think it<FP char=\"’\">\'</FP>s not feasible <FP char=\"…\">...</FP> is there any other way? Please give me an answer !</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.68.253.110',0,1),(218,46,14,'2019-01-22 09:23:34',64,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"46\" displayname=\"uranus97s2\" id=\"217\" number=\"13\" username=\"uranus97s2\">@uranus97s2#217</POSTMENTION></p>\n\n<p>I barely used Docker, but you should be able to find the location of the pulled files, in that case, you should be able to copy the files. If not, copy and paste the keystore content is another workaround.</p> \n\n<p>However, please note that, if you wanna keep the original account information (including the balance, etc), you should copy the database as well (which includes all the files in <FP char=\"“\">\"</FP>data.db<FP char=\"”\">\"</FP>).</p> \n</r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'108.162.226.26',0,1),(219,46,15,'2019-01-22 10:36:54',167,'comment','<t><p>thank you ! Have a nice day.</p></t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.68.254.159',0,1),(220,48,1,'2019-01-22 11:44:29',84,'comment','<r>\n\n<p>1月10号，我们在“星云社区论坛”举办了首次“星云测试网开发者激励活动（DIP）有奖问答”，为大家详细讲解了测试网开发者激励活动的规则细节。<br/>\n <br/>\n星云链创始人徐义吉、星云研究院院长范学鹏博士在线解答了大家的疑惑，回答了社区成员普遍关心的问题。本次有奖问答中，社区热心小伙伴积极参与，提出了很多高质量问题和建议。<br/>\n <br/>\n根据活动规则，星云团队将挑选出10位提出建设性问题和建议的论坛账号，给予NAS 奖励，每个账号奖励5NAS。<br/>\n <br/>\n获奖名单如下：<br/>\n<USERMENTION displayname=\"llp\" id=\"114\" username=\"llp\">@llp</USERMENTION> <br/>\n<USERMENTION displayname=\"mook\" id=\"117\" username=\"mook\">@mook</USERMENTION> <br/>\n<USERMENTION displayname=\"zhaozeen\" id=\"138\" username=\"zhaozeen\">@zhaozeen</USERMENTION> <br/>\n<USERMENTION displayname=\"dappwind\" id=\"139\" username=\"dappwind\">@dappwind</USERMENTION> <br/>\n<USERMENTION displayname=\"chenshiyan\" id=\"116\" username